SELECT MAX(salary) AS second_highest_salary
FROM Employee
WHERE salary < (
    SELECT MAX(salary)
    FROM Employee
);

To rename columns in a pandas DataFrame, I use the rename() method by passing a dictionary where keys are old column names and values are new column names.
df = df.rename(columns={
    'old_name': 'new_name',
    'Age': 'Customer_Age'
})
